<TITLE> Finance ministry gets 925 letters, emails in feedback to budget </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 18 (bdnews24.com) -- The Ministry of Finance has received 925 letters and emails in feedback to the budget proposed for fiscal 2007-08, an adviser said Monday. Finance adviser AB Mirza Azizul Islam Monday told reporters in his office that the ministry would prepare a summary after reviewing the opinions. The adviser said his ministry would prepare a set of recommendations on the basis of the opinions that would be placed at the meeting of the council of advisers. Azizul said he would talk to reporters at a news conference on June 30 after president Iajuddin Ahmed signs the budget files. The president is expected to pass the budget on June 28, he said. bdnews24.c
